  <!-- ── What is Machining Coolant? ── -->
  <h2 id="what-is-machining-coolant">What is Machining Coolant?</h2>

  <p>Industrial operations with machining operations such as <a href="https://www.sme.org/technologies/machining-metal-cutting/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">metal cutting</a>, grinding, milling, etc., use <a href="https://www.sme.org/technologies/articles/2012/managing-shop-coolants-and-chips/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">coolants</a> for product consistency and operational durability. Therefore the quality of the machining coolant is an essential factor for efficient machining operations.</p>

  <p>Many companies do not continually measure the contamination levels in their machining coolants. They have learned by trial and error that no problems will occur in the following machining stages by changing the coolant once a month or so.</p>

  <p>Changing coolants just because they are dirty is an old-fashioned approach. It is also a messy and time-consuming task. With an industrial fluid centrifuge, you can control the contamination in the coolant tank.</p>

  <p>There are many benefits to having a <a href="https://www.mscdirect.com/betterMRO/metalworking/5-reasons-keep-machining-coolant-clean" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Clean Machining Coolant</a>.</p>

