  <!-- ── Disadvantages ── -->
  <h3 id="coolant-centrifuge-disadvantages">Disadvantages</h3>

  <p>Despite the advantages listed above, there are certain disadvantages to centrifuges for coolant recycling. The following are some of the limitations of centrifuges.</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Capital Cost:</strong> Coolant centrifuges are capital-intensive equipment. Though their payback period is relatively short, the initial cost can be daunting to first-time customers.</li>
    <li><strong>Sophisticated Construction:</strong> An industrial centrifuge is a high-speed machine with intricate moving parts. It is a mechanical separating machine that requires <a href="/industrial-disc-centrifuge-repair/">maintenance</a>. Comparatively, a filter is much simpler to operate than a centrifuge.</li>
    <li><strong>Auxiliary Utilities Needed:</strong> A <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">self-cleaning centrifuge</a> requires clean, potable water to operate the sludge ejection system. In addition, a centrifuge may also require compressed air (for sludge pumps). Filters don't need these additional utilities.</li>
  </ul>

